column2: Abdominal aortic aneurysms often grow slowly and usually without symptoms, making them difficult to detect. Some aneurysms will never rupture. Many start small and stay small, although many expand over time. Others expand quickly. Predicting how fast an abdominal aortic aneurysm may enlarge is difficult.

column2: An indication of simple absence seizure is a vacant stare, which may be mistaken for a lapse in attention that lasts 10 to 15 seconds, without any subsequent confusion, headache or drowsiness. Signs and symptoms of absence seizures include:
column3: Sudden stop in motion without falling
column9: The first time you notice a seizure
column10: If this is a new type of seizure
column11: If the seizures continue to occur despite being placed on anti-seizure medication
column12: If you observe prolonged automatic behaviors — activities such as eating or moving without awareness — or prolonged confusion, possible symptoms of a condition called absence status epilepticus
column13: After any seizure lasting more than five minutes

column2: Although it's possible to have no signs or symptoms with an Achilles tendon rupture, most people experience:
column3: Pain, possibly severe, and swelling near your heel
column4: An inability to bend your foot downward or "push off" the injured leg when you walk
column5: An inability to stand on your toes on the injured leg
column6: A popping or snapping sound when the injury occurs
